Dataset

The dataset and guided project structure were provided through the Maven Analytics Power BI Desktop course. The dataset is based on Microsoft’s AdventureWorks sample database.

The data includes sales, customer, product, territory, and return-related information.

Project Objectives
Clean and transform raw data using Power Query.
Build a relational data model using fact and dimension tables.
Create calculated columns and DAX measures.
Track KPIs such as revenue, profit, orders, and return rates.
Compare business performance across regions and product categories.
Identify product trends and high-value customers.
Design an interactive dashboard for business decision-making.
Dashboard Features
Executive dashboard with key KPIs.
Regional performance analysis.
Product-level trend analysis.
Customer detail view to identify high-value customers.
Return analysis and product performance monitoring.
Interactive filters, slicers, and drill-through navigation.
Clean dashboard design for business reporting.
Key Skills Practiced
Data cleaning and transformation in Power Query.
Relational data modeling with fact and dimension tables.
DAX measures for KPI tracking and business analysis.
Dashboard design and data visualization.
Sales, customer, product, and regional performance analysis.
Turning raw data into business insights.
Key Insights
Compared sales, profit, orders, and returns across different business areas.
Identified strong-performing products, regions, and customer groups.
Analyzed customer-level data to highlight high-value customers.
Used interactive visuals to support KPI monitoring and management reporting.
Practiced translating business data into clear, decision-supporting dashboards.
Business Value

This dashboard helps business users monitor company performance, understand sales trends, compare regional results, and analyze customer and product behavior. The project demonstrates how Power BI can support business intelligence, KPI reporting, and data-driven decision-making.

